      <description>&lt;nav id=&#34;TableOfContents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#750-million-years-of-vitamin-d---a-little-history---without-hysteria&#34;&gt;750 million years of vitamin D - A little history - without hysteria&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#see-related-in-vitamindwiki&#34;&gt;See related in VitaminDWiki&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;750-million-years-of-vitamin-d---a-little-history---without-hysteria&#34;&gt;750 million years of vitamin D - A little history - without hysteria&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://borsche.de/page/vitamind_22&#34;&gt;Lorenz Borsche, April 2022&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h5 id=&#34;in-the-beginning-there-was-the-light&#34;&gt;In the beginning there was the light&lt;/h5&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;750-500 million years ago, the &amp;ldquo;vitamin D&amp;rdquo; system evolved in organisms. Vitamin D3 is actually not a vitamin, but a secosteroid. Steroids are lipids, and they are often derived from the first of all steroids: Cholesterol, an essential basic building block of our cell walls. Well-known steroids include estrogen, testosterone, and cortisone, to name a few.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
